result.execSummary:
The defendant Ricardo Velasco Salinas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 2:58 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Ricardo Velasco Salinas in court, in-custody, with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Rick Kissell sworn as Spanish Interpreter.
ADA Hall submits information; Atty Dahnert indicates that she has not completed waiver form
Recess: 2:59 pm for Atty Dahnert to complete paperwork - Reconvene: 3:04 pm
Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent.  
Mr. Velasco Salinas waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
Arraignment:--service of Information admitted, reading waived--maximum penalties recited

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Count #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court dismisses Counts #1, #3 & #4

On Count #2, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--To comply with treatment or counseling per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--Comply with all family court orders regarding child support
--Make all child support payments on time
--Make all payments on arrearages according to the child support orders
--Within 5 days of sentencing (or, if in custody, within 5 business days of release) defendant shall report to the child support agency Jefferson County Courthouse, 311 S. Center Ave.  Jefferson Room 219 to complete a case management meeting
--Advise child support office of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such a change
--To pay $468 extradition fees
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
Court orders Child Support and arrearages to be paid prior to fees and costs
All payments toward child support and arrearages to be paid through: WISCONSIN SUPPORT COLLECTION TRUST FUND, PO Box 74200 Milwaukee, WI 53274-0200 NOT through DOC
